N2  - This study extended previous empirical work on corporate political activity by examining corporate involvement with the U.S. International Trade Commission. Our findings suggest that organizational slack is an important determinant of corporate political strategy and that the presence of a large number of politically inactive firms in an industry does not deter other firms from becoming politically active.
AB  - This study extended previous empirical work on corporate political activity by examining corporate involvement with the U.S. International Trade Commission. Our findings suggest that organizational slack is an important determinant of corporate political strategy and that the presence of a large number of politically inactive firms in an industry does not deter other firms from becoming politically active.
