N2  - This study examined the moderating effects of stimulus-screening skills and job complexity on relations between environmental characteristics and employee reactions. Employees exhibited the lowest performance and satisfaction when their jobs were low in complexity, their screening skills were weak, and they worked in dense areas, areas with few enclosures, or close to other employees.
